docs.lead_paragraph: The steamship North Star, Capt. R. A. WAMAEK, of the Independent Line, left New York on the 5th, at 3 P.M. From the 5th to the 9th she was favored with fine weather, the remainder of the passage was accompanied with a heavy sea and easterly winds. Arrived at Aspinwall on the 13th at 11 P.M., after a passage of 8 days and 8 hours.

docs.lead_paragraph: STREET-PREACHING.--There was street-preaching yesterday afternoon at Williamsburg, at the usual time and place. The largest number present at any time was about six or seven hundred, all of whom behaved in an orderly manner. Two men, who were arguing on religious matters, were about coming to blows, when they were arrested and taken to the lock-up.
